/F2 18 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 738 Tm
(Constrained Decoding for Executable Text-to-SQL) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 688 Tm
(Title and Motivation) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 656 Tm
(This project studies whether constrained decoding can improve text-to-SQL generation by) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 641 Tm
(forcing outputs to stay closer to valid WikiSQL query structure. The motivation is) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 626 Tm
(practical: a fine-tuned language model may still generate malformed SQL, hallucinated schema) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 611 Tm
(items, or invalid clause structures. Constrained decoding is meant to reduce those failures) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 596 Tm
(by limiting what the model can output at generation time.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 567 Tm
(Task Definition and Proposed Method) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 535 Tm
(The task is natural-language question to SQL generation on WikiSQL. We compare four) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 520 Tm
(settings:) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 491 Tm
(- Base model) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 476 Tm
(- Fine-tuned model) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 461 Tm
(- Base model with constrained decoding) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 446 Tm
(- Fine-tuned model with constrained decoding) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 417 Tm
(The base model is `google/flan-t5-base`. Fine-tuning is done with LoRA adapters using PEFT.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 402 Tm
(The constrained method restricts decoding to a tighter WikiSQL-style SQL template so the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 387 Tm
(output stays closer to `SELECT ... FROM ... [WHERE ...];` forms using schema-aware columns,) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 372 Tm
(the correct table id, and restricted operators.) Tj
