(Discussion) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 307 Tm
(The clearest result is that fine-tuning substantially improves performance over the base) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 292 Tm
(model. The base model produced no syntactically valid outputs in this evaluation subset,) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 277 Tm
(while the fine-tuned model reached 72% syntactic validity and 29% exact match at temperature) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 262 Tm
(0.0.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 233 Tm
(Temperature matters. For the fine-tuned model, both validity and exact match were best at) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 218 Tm
(temperature 0.0 and degraded as temperature increased. This is consistent with the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 203 Tm
(expectation that deterministic decoding is more suitable for structured generation tasks) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 188 Tm
(like SQL.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 159 Tm
(Constrained decoding produced mixed outcomes. It did not outperform the fine-tuned model.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 144 Tm
(However, it was more stable across temperatures: the fine-tuned constrained model stayed in) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 129 Tm
(the 0.56 to 0.59 validity range, while the unconstrained fine-tuned model dropped from 0.72) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 114 Tm
(at temperature 0.0 to 0.39 at temperature 1.0. This suggests constrained decoding can) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 99 Tm
(regularize output structure, but in this implementation it restricted the model too) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 84 Tm
(aggressively and reduced exact correctness.) Tj
