/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 738 Tm
(The main conclusion is that fine-tuning was the strongest contributor to performance, while) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 723 Tm
(constrained decoding introduced a tradeoff: somewhat more stable structural behavior across) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 708 Tm
(temperatures, but lower best-case validity and lower exact match than unconstrained fine-) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 693 Tm
(tuned decoding.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 664 Tm
(Conclusion) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 632 Tm
(This project demonstrates that:) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 603 Tm
(- Fine-tuning `flan-t5-base` with LoRA is effective for WikiSQL text-to-SQL generation.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 588 Tm
(- Low-temperature decoding gives the strongest performance for structured SQL outputs.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 573 Tm
(- Constrained decoding is promising in principle, but its effectiveness depends heavily on) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 558 Tm
(  how tightly the constraint matches the task.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 543 Tm
(- In our implementation, the best-performing configuration was the unconstrained fine-) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 528 Tm
(  tuned model at temperature 0.0.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 499 Tm
(Overall, the project shows that model adaptation through fine-tuning is highly beneficial,) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 484 Tm
(while constrained decoding remains a meaningful but challenging research direction for) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 469 Tm
(executable text-to-SQL generation.) Tj
ET
